"NOT FOUND"|"10. ut *** expugnarent, clause of purpose, introduced by eo consilio, with which it is in apposition. The secondary tense of the conclusion requires the imperfect possent and pluperfect potuissent in place of the future poterunt and future perfect potuerint. They will storm the fort if they can (if they shall be able); but if they cannot (if they shall not have been able), they will lay waste the lands."

