"NOT FOUND"|"concedendum, sc. id, referring to iter per provinciam facere. The studentwill observe how frequent is the use of the impersonal. In such a use the mere verbal act is brought into prominence without reference to the actor, e.g. concedendum, concessions must be made; but no mention is made of who must make them, for that is sufficiently apparent; acriter pugnatum, there was a hot fight, but no reference to the combatants."

