"ID HOC facilius iis persuasit, quod undique loci natura helvetii continentur: una ex parte flumine rheno latissimo atque altissimo, qui agrum helvetium a germanis dividit; altera ex parte monte iura altissimo, qui est inter sequanos et helvetios; tertia lacu lemanno et flumine rhodano, qui provinciam nostram ab helvetiis dividit."|"id hoc facilius eis persuasit, he persuaded them the more easily to this; literally, he persuaded this to them,***hoc, ablative of cause, referring to the clause beginning with quod. So in English *the more easily,*** the is an instrumental case of our Anglo-Saxon pronoun se. Hence the literal meaning is 4 by that more easily,*** an expression which corresponds to the Latin hoc facilius."

