"NOT FOUND"|"1. ipsis, sc. Gallis."

"NOT FOUND"|"ne *** adficerentur. ne, after verbs of fearing, is to be rendered that or lest. The origin of the use of ne in expressions of fear probably goes back to the form of a wish, e.g. ne veniat; metuo, ***may he not come ; I fear (he will),*** came to mean *** I fear that he will come.*** ut veniat; metuo, *** may he come ; I fear (he will not),*** came to mean, *** I fear he will not come.***in tanta multitudine. The in expresses cause: since so many were in the surrender."

