"NOT FOUND"|"exustis. The Latin language was deficient in a perfect active participle. The means employed to compensate for this part of the verb are : (1) The perfect participle of a deponent verb; e.g. eodem usi consilio. (2) The ablative absolute, as here. (3) A temporal clause."

