"NOT FOUND"|"81. 1. Haeduis. The dative for the ablative of separation. This dative, which occurs with certain compounds of ab, de, ex, is best explained as the dative of disadvantage, going with the whole idea of the sentence, and not merely with the verb; i.e. as far as the Haedui were concerned, their freedom would be wrested away from them."

