"NOT FOUND"|"19. vacare, to he empty; cf. patere, to lie open, chap. 2 ; licere, to he permitted, chap. 7 ; cavere, to he on one's guard, chap. 14; tacere, to he silent, chap. 17. Do these verbs assert action or state ? Are they transitive or intransitive ? How many English words must be used to express the meaning of each one ?"

